The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Oct. 7: The rate of inflation inched up to 3.97 per cent during the week ended September 24 from 3.75 per cent a week ago, mainly due to a rise in the prices of industrial fuel and manufactured products. Food items, however, became cheaper. Though the inflation rate neared 4 per cent, it was still lower than 7.33 per cent a year ago. Last week, finance minister P. Chidambaram said inflation is expected to be within ?tolerable limits?.

 New Delhi, Oct. 7: The Centre?s tax collections grew 21 per cent at over Rs 1,45,000 crore in the first half of 2005-06. While direct taxes were up 28 per cent at Rs 58,052 crore, indirect taxes rose 17 per cent to Rs 87,221 crore.

 Mumbai, Oct. 7: The government has approved Asian Development Bank?s proposal to raise $400 million equivalent of rupee loans in India through rupee bonds and cross currency routes for funding infrastructure and housing projects.

 New Delhi, Oct. 7: GSM-based cellular operators have crossed the 50-million milestone by adding 2 million subscribers in September. 

 New Delhi, Oct. 7: The Prime Minister?s economic advisory council has suggested to the revenue department to refund the service tax paid by export-oriented units within a definite time frame. 




